passages.text: Australia | Technology & Information Services PEXA Group

Operating EBITDA missed consensus by \(3\%\) on a like- for- like basis, ie after adding back Optima Legal interest income. The midpoint of FY26 EBITDA guidance range implies a \(9\%\) downgrade to consensus forecast.
FY25 result. Operating EBITDA missed consensus by \(3\%\) on a LFL basis, driven by losses in the UK.

- Australia: Revenue grew \(7.5\%\) to \(\) 313m\(, while EBITDA added\)8.4\%\(to\)\\(172.5m\) . Transaction volume in 2H was strong (+3.4% YoY vs mkt +2.9%) driven by refinance (+16.5% growth vs mkt 18.4%) while PXA's transfer volume was flat (vs mkt -1%). 2H25 average price of\)\\(78.5\) was \(2.7\%\) higher than 2H24. National rollout is complete, with market share sitting at 90%. AU Exchange expenses grew \(7\%\) in FY25 due to continued investment in cyber security and resilience. AU Capex was 10% lower than FY24. International: Revenue grew \(15.4\%\) on a pro-forma basis, driven by strong S&P revenue and positive FX impacts. Smoove revenue grew \(23\%\) on a pro-forma basis and achieved EBITDA breakeven in 2H, Smoove maintained its \(1.5\%\) market share. Opex was \(1\%\) higher on a pro-forma basis. Implementation with NatWest is now underway, with re-mo transactions anticipated to begin in 2H FY26, followed by S&P by the end of CY 2026. Digital Solutions: Rev increased \(21\%\) to \(\) 19.1m\(while Op EBITDA was marginally negative at\)- 30.3m\(, improving\)\\(6.3m\) on FY24. As previously announced, PXA is undergoing a strategic review of the Digital Solutions business.
Outlook commentary: PXA expects steady growth in the Australian Market as rates normalise. UK market is expected to return to more normal levels of growth.

- Group revenue \(\) 405-430m\( (3-9\% growth) (cons\)\\(436m)\)- Group EBITDA before associates margin of \(32-35\%\) , implying \(\) 130-150m\(, or if we add\)\\(3m\) for Optima Legal interest income: \(\) 133m-153m\(, the midpoint of which is\)9\%\(below consensus of\)\\(156m\).- Group Core NPAT \(\) 5-15m\( (cons\)\\(17.1m)\)- Group Capex \(\) 60-65m\( (cons\)\\(68.1m)\)- International operating cash flow \(\) 59\(to\)\\(63m\) , higher than the \(\) 57.7m\(in FY25.

PEXA GroupPEXA Group is primarily an operator of digital property settlements in Australia through the PEXA Exchange and is pursuing growth opportunities in international markets. The PEXA Exchange is an Electronic Lodgment Network Operator (ELNO) facilitating electronic lodgment and settlement of property transactions through a platform connecting property market stakeholders. PEXA was established in 2010 in Melbourne, Australia.

We value PEXA based on a SOTP DCF valuation. Key assumptions underpinning our DCF valuation are DCF to FY33E with \(8.6\%\) WACC, \(4.5\%\) risk- free rate, 1.1 beta, and \(4.0\%\) terminal growth rate. Key risks include increased competition, new regulation impacting market structures, higher- than- expected investment required to grow the UK, and economic conditions affecting property markets.

Jefferies Franchise Picks will include only Buy rated stocks and the number can vary depending on analyst recommendations for inclusion.
